        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 10:36AM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1036 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles southeast of Donnelly to near Big Creek
Summit to near Warm Lake to Sulphur Creek Ranch. Movement was north
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Landmark, Warm Lake, and Paddy Flat Work Center around 1040 AM
MDT.
Halfway Station and Poverty Flat Campground around 1050 AM MDT.
Lake Fork Guard Station and Pistol Rock around 1100 AM MDT.
Krassel Work Center around 1110 AM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
